# Inferential Statistics on Student Performance Dataset

##  Overview

This project demonstrates the application of key **inferential statistics techniques** on a student performance dataset.
The goal is to understand how to draw conclusions about a population using sample data.

---

##  Objectives

* Apply core statistical methods:

  * Confidence Interval
  * One Sample T-Test
  * One Sample Z-Test
  * Chi-Square Test
  * One-Way ANOVA
  * Two-Way ANOVA
* Interpret **p-values and statistical significance**
* Build strong intuition for real-world data analysis

---

## 📁 Dataset Features

* Demographics: gender, age, race/ethnicity
* Education: parental level of education
* Behavior: study hours, attendance, test preparation
* Scores: math, reading, writing

---

## ⚙️ Techniques Used

* Hypothesis Testing
* Statistical Inference
* Data Analysis with Python
* Libraries: NumPy, Pandas, SciPy, Statsmodels

